1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:02,503
♪

2
00:00:02,536 --> 00:00:03,737
Joseph: This room looks like

3
00:00:03,770 --> 00:00:06,506
it was on the receiving end
of a tornado.

4
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:10,210
I don’t understand how this hole
could be perfectly spherical.

5
00:00:10,244 --> 00:00:12,613
What is going on?

6
00:00:12,646 --> 00:00:14,481
Kakyoin: I’m not sure,
but the destruction

7
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:15,916
spreads into
the other room, too.

8
00:00:15,949 --> 00:00:17,851
Joseph: It’s safe to say
avdol and the others

9
00:00:17,885 --> 00:00:20,488
made contact with the enemy.

10
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:21,856
Here we go.

11
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:23,391
Break down this door, jotaro.

12
00:00:23,423 --> 00:00:25,492
- We’re going in.
- Jotaro: Roger.

13
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:27,661
Star platinum: Ora!

14
00:00:32,199 --> 00:00:34,201
♪

15
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:38,238
( Singing in Japanese )

16
00:00:59,626 --> 00:01:02,596
Polnareff: Au revoir, iggy.

17
00:01:02,629 --> 00:01:03,797
( Iggy yelps )

18
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:07,801
( Whimpers )

19
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:14,908
( Silence )

20
00:01:16,877 --> 00:01:18,312
( Clang echoes )

21
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:30,257
♪

22
00:01:31,658 --> 00:01:33,660
( Cool ice panting )

23
00:01:37,331 --> 00:01:38,499
( Grunts )

24
00:01:45,906 --> 00:01:49,309
Polnareff, the blood
that stains my body

25
00:01:49,343 --> 00:01:52,680
is avdol’s handiwork,
not yours.

26
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:54,715
( Panting )

27
00:01:54,748 --> 00:01:57,818
My plan was to eradicate
you both simultaneously,

28
00:01:57,851 --> 00:02:01,955
but due to avdol’s intervention,
your demise was postponed.

29
00:02:01,989 --> 00:02:05,359
Anyone else would have
instinctively saved himself

30
00:02:05,392 --> 00:02:06,894
over risking life and limb

31
00:02:06,927 --> 00:02:09,563
to come to the aid
of an oblivious comrade.

32
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:12,899
that alone makes him
responsible for my injuries.

33
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,968
He may have been able
to injure me,

34
00:02:15,002 --> 00:02:18,405
but it’ll take far more than
that to send me to the grave.

35
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:21,474
Now i’ll set my sights
on the other interlopers.

36
00:02:21,508 --> 00:02:24,411
i’ll kill them
in the name of lord dio.

37
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:29,383
- ( Gasps )
- Polnareff: Damn it.

38
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:31,818
I told you not to use
your stand, iggy,

39
00:02:31,852 --> 00:02:34,755
but you just had to show off,
didn’t you?

40
00:02:34,788 --> 00:02:36,556
Stupid dog.

41
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:38,559
Why’d you have to do it?

42
00:02:38,592 --> 00:02:39,827
Cool ice: Polnareff?

43
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:42,329
Narrator: As far as cool ice
was concerned,

44
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:44,698
iggy was nothing more
than a filthy stray

45
00:02:44,731 --> 00:02:46,533
without resolve or pride,

46
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:50,805
but by its very nature, a stand
is a manifestation of the soul,

47
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:53,541
and iggy’s had acted
of its own volition

48
00:02:53,574 --> 00:02:56,410
with something compelling it
from deep within.

49
00:02:56,443 --> 00:02:57,744
( Iggy gags )

50
00:02:57,778 --> 00:02:58,979
( Polnareff gasps )

51
00:03:01,415 --> 00:03:05,419
His sand, its spirit is gone.

52
00:03:05,452 --> 00:03:06,954
How could this have happened?

53
00:03:06,987 --> 00:03:08,388
Damn it.

54
00:03:08,422 --> 00:03:10,991
All that’s left
is a lifeless husk.

55
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,727
The chill of death
is in the air,

56
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,997
and another life
has been cut short far too soon.

57
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:20,400
Why am I the only one
who survived?

58
00:03:20,434 --> 00:03:22,469
( Chorus vocalizing )

59
00:03:22,503 --> 00:03:24,772
Ig--( Sobbing )

60
00:03:24,805 --> 00:03:27,608
Iggy!

61
00:03:27,641 --> 00:03:29,910
( Cool ice roars )

62
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:33,780
Polnareff: You’re too slow
for your own good, cool ice,

63
00:03:33,814 --> 00:03:35,516
but you know something?

64
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,717
You’re right.

65
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,418
I had some pretty
selfless friends, huh?

66
00:03:38,452 --> 00:03:40,554
I was supposed
to look out for iggy,

67
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:41,988
but instead he saved my ass.

68
00:03:42,022 --> 00:03:44,057
( Silver chariot grunts )

69
00:03:58,472 --> 00:03:59,540
Polnareff: Damn it.

70
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:02,509
How could this be happening?

71
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:06,480
I’ve only just begun to realize
what he meant to me.

72
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:08,815
This is how it always is.

73
00:04:08,849 --> 00:04:11,719
i don’t get it
until after they’re gone.

74
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:14,121
You were a miserable
little mutt from the start,

75
00:04:14,154 --> 00:04:16,456
but despite that,
you never failed

76
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,026
to find new ways to impress me.

77
00:04:19,059 --> 00:04:22,529
You were a proud bastard who
lived life by your own rules,

78
00:04:22,563 --> 00:04:23,998
and we were the ones

79
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:26,934
who mistook your self-respect
as indifference.

80
00:04:26,967 --> 00:04:30,838
I told you not to save me.

81
00:04:30,871 --> 00:04:34,942
Damn it, flea bag, why’d you
have to be so stubborn?

82
00:04:35,976 --> 00:04:38,645
( Crying )

83
00:04:48,822 --> 00:04:51,525
( Cream growling )

84
00:04:53,994 --> 00:04:55,562
Polnareff: I knew it.

85
00:04:55,596 --> 00:04:58,966
I’ve figured out
what you are, cool ice.

86
00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:00,667
( Cream yells )

87
00:05:00,701 --> 00:05:02,603
( Silver chariot yells )

88
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:03,937
( Cool ice screams )

89
00:05:05,706 --> 00:05:07,074
♪

90
00:05:19,086 --> 00:05:21,589
( Cool ice growls )

91
00:05:21,622 --> 00:05:24,458
Polnareff: I knew there was
something was strange about you.

92
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:25,892
You’re an immortal.

93
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,128
Dio somehow found a way
to transform you.

94
00:05:28,162 --> 00:05:29,597
( Cool ice roars )

95
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:36,704
( Gasps )

96
00:05:36,737 --> 00:05:39,006
W-what the hell is this?

97
00:05:39,039 --> 00:05:41,508
What’s happening to me?!

98
00:05:41,542 --> 00:05:43,844
polnareff:
Obviously your precious master

99
00:05:43,877 --> 00:05:46,179
made the changes
without your knowledge.

100
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:48,215
He gave you his blood,
didn’t he?

101
00:05:48,248 --> 00:05:51,785
Guess he left out the part about
you turning into a vampire.

102
00:05:51,818 --> 00:05:55,055
- ( Cool ice gasps )
- You’re just like dio now,

103
00:05:55,088 --> 00:05:58,258
a disgusting, soulless vampire.

104
00:05:58,292 --> 00:06:00,861
Cool ice: You bastard!

105
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:04,665
( Gasps )

106
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,702
Polnareff: Since you’re
only feeling it now,

107
00:06:08,735 --> 00:06:12,172
the change must have started
after I stabbed you. Come on.

108
00:06:12,206 --> 00:06:15,276
You made a vow to protect
your lord and master, right?

109
00:06:15,309 --> 00:06:17,278
What are you waiting for?
bring it.

110
00:06:17,311 --> 00:06:18,612
( Cool ice snarls )

111
00:06:18,645 --> 00:06:20,647
Polnareff: Go on! Do your worst!

112
00:06:20,681 --> 00:06:23,651
Hey, what’s the holdup,
cool ice? I’m waiting.

113
00:06:23,684 --> 00:06:26,854
cool ice:
You’re not going to defeat me!

114
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:29,022
polnareff:
Now go to hell, asshole.

115
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:42,102
♪

116
00:07:04,191 --> 00:07:06,193
( Gasping )

117
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:14,601
- ( Avdol grunts )
- ( Iggy grunts )

118
00:07:15,636 --> 00:07:18,005
Polnareff: A-avdol, wait.

119
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:19,139
I-iggy!

120
00:07:19,173 --> 00:07:21,308
( Groans )

121
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:32,119
Was--was that my imagination?

122
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,788
Or was it really...

123
00:07:39,693 --> 00:07:42,963
I don’t have time
to sit and ponder.

124
00:07:42,996 --> 00:07:44,264
All that matters now

125
00:07:44,298 --> 00:07:47,067
is making it upstairs
and finding dio.

126
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,035
Mourning can wait.

127
00:07:49,069 --> 00:07:52,372
I can’t fall apart after
everything they sacrificed.

128
00:07:54,074 --> 00:07:56,643
( Gasping )

129
00:07:58,946 --> 00:08:00,915
( Overlapping chatter )

130
00:08:00,948 --> 00:08:04,084
Narrator: Japan.
43 days had passed

131
00:08:04,117 --> 00:08:06,953
since jojo and the others
began their journey to Egypt.

132
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,122
Suzie q: Rosas, stop the car.

133
00:08:09,156 --> 00:08:11,125
Hit the brakes.
I want to get out.

134
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:15,496
Rosas: Madame joestar,
I don’t mean to overstep,

135
00:08:15,529 --> 00:08:18,432
but is now really the best time
to stop at a soba stand?

136
00:08:18,465 --> 00:08:19,633
Suzie q: Well, of course.

137
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,501
I haven’t been to Japan
in a while.

138
00:08:21,535 --> 00:08:24,371
I’d like to grab a quick bite
before visiting my little girl.

139
00:08:24,404 --> 00:08:27,274
Hon, would you be a dear
and hold on to my turtle?

140
00:08:28,709 --> 00:08:30,444
rosas:
Please, madam, you mustn’t.

141
00:08:30,477 --> 00:08:33,080
Places such as these
are for common businessmen.

142
00:08:33,113 --> 00:08:36,183
Ladies of your pedigree should
only dine at fine restaurants.

143
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:38,618
I am begging you, madam.
Don’t go in there.

144
00:08:38,652 --> 00:08:40,154
Suzie q: Lighten up, rosas.

145
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:42,322
it’s so quaint,
I just have to record it.

146
00:08:42,356 --> 00:08:45,559
Oh, the local flavor
is simply to die for.

147
00:08:45,592 --> 00:08:47,594
Oh, this’ll be a good shot.

148
00:08:49,563 --> 00:08:51,432
( Squeals )

149
00:08:51,465 --> 00:08:52,967
( Rosas sighs )

150
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,401
- Guard: Mr. Rosas.
- Rosas: Huh?

151
00:08:54,434 --> 00:08:56,336
guard: Judging by
the madam’s cavalier attitude,

152
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:59,139
I take it you’ve not told her
about holly’s condition.

153
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,541
( Rosas sighs )

154
00:09:01,575 --> 00:09:03,510
suzie q: Hey,
what’s the holdup, rosas?

155
00:09:03,544 --> 00:09:04,945
Get over here!

156
00:09:04,978 --> 00:09:06,947
rosas: Oh,
i’m right behind you, madam.

157
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,982
♪

158
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:14,354
No, I haven’t uttered
a single word.

159
00:09:14,388 --> 00:09:16,290
As far as she knows,

160
00:09:16,323 --> 00:09:19,326
her daughter is battling
a severe case of pneumonia.

161
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:23,163
I’ve worked for the joestar
family for the past 30 years.

162
00:09:23,197 --> 00:09:25,132
As for miss Holly,
i’ve known her

163
00:09:25,165 --> 00:09:27,968
since she was a little girl
in grade school.

164
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:31,571
Believe me, I know that I
have to tell her the truth,

165
00:09:31,605 --> 00:09:34,241
but I just
don’t have the heart.

166
00:09:34,274 --> 00:09:37,377
even coming to Japan
hasn’t given me the courage.

167
00:09:37,411 --> 00:09:40,314
Guard: Holly doesn’t have long.
If she’s not saved,

168
00:09:40,347 --> 00:09:42,749
she’ll likely die
within the next few days.

169
00:09:42,783 --> 00:09:45,753
Would you prefer that I
told madam joestar, sir?

170
00:09:45,786 --> 00:09:50,024
Rosas: No, thank you, but i’ve
made my bed with the falsehoods

171
00:09:50,057 --> 00:09:52,593
i’ve told the madam,
and now I have to lie in it.

172
00:09:52,626 --> 00:09:55,195
I have to be the one
to inform her.

173
00:09:55,229 --> 00:09:56,430
( Guard sighs )

174
00:09:56,463 --> 00:09:58,465
rosas: Tell me,
are you absolutely sure

175
00:09:58,499 --> 00:10:01,769
the curse afflicting miss Holly
will be lifted if dio is killed?

176
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:05,506
Guard: I am. Dio’s demise
will end this. Trust me.

177
00:10:07,074 --> 00:10:08,442
holly’s body
is reacting to energy

178
00:10:08,475 --> 00:10:10,243
from something known as a stand,

179
00:10:10,277 --> 00:10:14,448
but only people with said stands
can observe the phenomenon.

180
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:18,251
Put simply, dio’s dark energy
is slowly destroying her,

181
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,687
but madam cannot see the stands.

182
00:10:20,721 --> 00:10:22,790
instead,
she’ll have to bear witness

183
00:10:22,823 --> 00:10:25,259
to her only daughter
in the throes of death.

184
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,462
she must know.
The time for secrets is over.

185
00:10:28,495 --> 00:10:31,064
Rosas: Yes. Yes, you’re right.

186
00:10:31,098 --> 00:10:32,466
Suzie q: There you are, rosas.

187
00:10:32,499 --> 00:10:34,267
what are you
still doing out here?

188
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:38,071
Instead of sulking around,
come have some curry udon.

189
00:10:38,105 --> 00:10:40,074
- ( Rosas sighs )
- ( Guard grunts )

190
00:10:40,107 --> 00:10:41,642
Rosas: Please, listen, madam.

191
00:10:41,675 --> 00:10:43,777
There is something
that I need to tell--

192
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,413
suzie q: Oh!
Oh, I must get some footage

193
00:10:46,446 --> 00:10:49,382
of this delightful little
health-drink vending machine.

194
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:51,118
Another good shot!

195
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:53,253
Would you like me
to get you one, rosas?

196
00:10:53,287 --> 00:10:55,489
Rosas: Wait! Madam joestar,
you have to stop this.

197
00:10:55,522 --> 00:10:58,225
Despite appearances,
those aren’t drinks. Madam,

198
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:00,127
please,
you have to listen to me!

199
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,095
Suzie q: My! What is it?

200
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:06,100
Rosas: Well, uh,
it’s about miss Holly.

201
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:08,302
suzie q: Ooh!
Look at this Japanese man’s

202
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:11,138
unique fashion sense.
very nice.

203
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:12,372
Hi there. How are you?

204
00:11:12,406 --> 00:11:14,475
Give me a big smile,
if you would.

205
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:17,144
Man: Huh? What the hell
are you doin’, lady?

206
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:19,579
Who gave you permission
to videotape me, huh?

207
00:11:19,613 --> 00:11:22,282
( Rosas screams )
Please, madam, get in the car.

208
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:24,652
- Suzie q: Nice to meet you.
- Man: Come back here, damn it!

209
00:11:24,685 --> 00:11:26,320
We’re not done!

210
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:28,856
I’ll be taking that camera
from you before you leave.

211
00:11:28,889 --> 00:11:32,426
Who do you think you are?!
You’re just a damn foreign hag.

212
00:11:32,459 --> 00:11:35,562
You lookin’ to see some blood
today, you rich bitch? Huh?!

213
00:11:35,596 --> 00:11:37,665
Rosas: All right, that’s enough.

214
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:40,501
I forbid you to lay
another finger on madam.

215
00:11:40,534 --> 00:11:42,236
( Man groans )

216
00:11:42,269 --> 00:11:43,704
( Crashing )

217
00:11:43,737 --> 00:11:45,672
rosas: Madam,
you should try learning

218
00:11:45,706 --> 00:11:47,675
a bit more
about Japanese culture.

219
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:48,676
Suzie q: Okay.

220
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:50,477
( Guard sighs )

221
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:53,313
Rosas: I couldn’t do it.

222
00:11:53,347 --> 00:11:56,250
I couldn’t tell her miss Holly
only has a few days left.

223
00:11:56,283 --> 00:11:57,684
It would break her heart,

224
00:11:57,718 --> 00:12:00,421
and that’s the last thing
I would ever want to do.

225
00:12:00,454 --> 00:12:02,456
♪

226
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:18,638
we’ve almost arrived,
and I still haven’t told her.

227
00:12:18,672 --> 00:12:20,908
I can’t put this off any longer.

228
00:12:20,941 --> 00:12:23,911
We’ll soon be in sight
of the kujo house.

229
00:12:23,944 --> 00:12:26,713
She needs to hear this from me.

230
00:12:26,747 --> 00:12:30,317
( Groaning )

231
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:31,685
Suzie q: It’s okay.

232
00:12:31,718 --> 00:12:34,321
I know there’s something
you want to tell me.

233
00:12:34,354 --> 00:12:36,690
You don’t need
to pretend anymore.

234
00:12:36,723 --> 00:12:39,426
i’m well aware
of what’s troubling you, rosas.

235
00:12:39,459 --> 00:12:42,629
My daughter’s life is
in grave danger, isn’t it?

236
00:12:42,663 --> 00:12:44,231
( Rosas and guard gasp )

237
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:49,436
♪

238
00:12:49,469 --> 00:12:52,238
Suzie q: I called Holly
from New York a few times.

239
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,807
She put on a brave face

240
00:12:53,841 --> 00:12:55,876
and pretended to be
cheerful and lively.

241
00:12:55,909 --> 00:12:59,813
She tried her best to convince
me it was only a mild cold.

242
00:12:59,847 --> 00:13:02,216
Whenever Joseph phoned,
he would tell me

243
00:13:02,249 --> 00:13:04,384
his business trip
kept him very busy,

244
00:13:04,418 --> 00:13:06,787
but that I had
nothing to worry about,

245
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:10,724
but I knew they were keeping
something important from me.

246
00:13:10,757 --> 00:13:12,726
deep down,
I knew something terrible

247
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:15,195
was happening
to my daughter and husband.

248
00:13:15,229 --> 00:13:17,932
I’ve been married to Joseph
for 50 years now,

249
00:13:17,965 --> 00:13:20,968
and my sweet Holly
is my own flesh and blood.

250
00:13:21,001 --> 00:13:22,569
( Men sigh )

251
00:13:22,603 --> 00:13:24,872
Suzie q: I never pressed them
for more information,

252
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:26,907
because I was afraid
of what they’d say.

253
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:29,976
I wanted nothing more than
to see my precious daughter,

254
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:33,714
but the thought of what i’d
find here was almost too much.

255
00:13:33,747 --> 00:13:35,282
Guard: You know this much,

256
00:13:35,315 --> 00:13:37,984
so you also have the right
to know the rest.

257
00:13:38,018 --> 00:13:41,288
As it stands, your daughter only
has a few days left to live.

258
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:43,857
That’s why Mr. Joestar
and the others went to Egypt,

259
00:13:43,891 --> 00:13:45,860
to end the source
of her illness,

260
00:13:45,893 --> 00:13:48,262
but there’s been
no news for a while.

261
00:13:48,295 --> 00:13:50,831
rosas: Please,
can you find it in your heart

262
00:13:50,864 --> 00:13:52,966
to forgive me
for not telling you?

263
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,302
there was nothing
we could do for miss Holly,

264
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:58,305
so I wanted to spare you
from the pain, but I was wrong.

265
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:01,608
I should have told you.
It was cruel of me not to.

266
00:14:01,642 --> 00:14:02,676
( Crying )

267
00:14:02,709 --> 00:14:04,411
Suzie q: I don’t want to hear

268
00:14:04,444 --> 00:14:06,279
any more of that foolishness,
rosas.

269
00:14:06,313 --> 00:14:08,282
No matter how grim things seem,

270
00:14:08,315 --> 00:14:10,384
there’s still one thing
we can do for Holly.

271
00:14:10,417 --> 00:14:11,585
( Men gasp )

272
00:14:11,618 --> 00:14:13,887
♪

273
00:14:23,564 --> 00:14:24,765
( Holly gasps )

274
00:14:30,404 --> 00:14:32,773
( Chuckles )

275
00:14:32,806 --> 00:14:35,776
Suzie q: Hi, sweet girl.

276
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:46,353
Holly: I’m so glad you’re here.

277
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:49,256
Suzie q: Listen to me
very carefully, rosas.

278
00:14:49,289 --> 00:14:52,025
Right now, the one thing
we can do for my daughter

279
00:14:52,059 --> 00:14:53,894
is have faith.

280
00:14:53,927 --> 00:14:56,763
i don’t understand
everything that’s happening,

281
00:14:56,797 --> 00:14:58,766
but here’s what I do know.

282
00:14:58,799 --> 00:15:00,501
Joseph and my grandson jotaro

283
00:15:00,534 --> 00:15:02,569
are putting their lives
on the line

284
00:15:02,603 --> 00:15:04,038
in the hope of saving Holly,

285
00:15:04,071 --> 00:15:07,374
and I believe they will find
a way to do just that.

286
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:08,875
He’s never failed me,

287
00:15:08,909 --> 00:15:11,512
not once in the 50 years
I have known him.

288
00:15:11,545 --> 00:15:13,047
he’s kept
every promise he’s made

289
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,349
since the two of us
met in Italy.

290
00:15:15,382 --> 00:15:17,718
Once he’s made up his mind
to do something,

291
00:15:17,751 --> 00:15:19,820
nothing in this world
can stop him.

292
00:15:21,054 --> 00:15:23,757
Rest and believe in jotaro
and your father.

293
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,026
You’ll be better
before you know it,

294
00:15:26,059 --> 00:15:29,029
and our family
will be together once again.

295
00:15:29,062 --> 00:15:31,398
Holly: Thank you, mama.

296
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,600
( Rosas crying )

297
00:15:33,634 --> 00:15:35,936
Madam joestar, miss Holly,

298
00:15:35,969 --> 00:15:37,404
please hang in there.

299
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:39,439
( Crying )

300
00:15:42,042 --> 00:15:43,677
( Running footsteps )

301
00:15:45,078 --> 00:15:46,846
( Footsteps echoing )

302
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,883
Man: That cool ice,
Billie Jean,

303
00:15:49,917 --> 00:15:52,386
even d’arby younger--
( Laughs )

304
00:15:52,419 --> 00:15:55,289
I knew they were nothing
but incompetent fools.

305
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:00,961
( Laughing )

306
00:16:03,197 --> 00:16:04,398
I shouldn’t laugh,

307
00:16:04,431 --> 00:16:06,833
but knowing
they got what they deserved

308
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,302
feels so satisfying!

309
00:16:08,335 --> 00:16:09,970
( Laughs )

310
00:16:10,003 --> 00:16:12,939
That’s what the fools get
for calling me a loser.

311
00:16:12,973 --> 00:16:16,176
But at least now we know
I wasn’t one after all.

312
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:18,179
Cool ice: Don’t be absurd.

313
00:16:18,212 --> 00:16:20,147
you can’t
possibly defeat the joestars

314
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:21,815
using that pathetic power.

315
00:16:21,849 --> 00:16:23,317
D’arby: Out of the way, loser.

316
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,018
vampire:
Hey, but that’s not fair!

317
00:16:25,052 --> 00:16:27,221
I want a chance
to fight them, too!

318
00:16:27,254 --> 00:16:29,857
Cool ice: You’re merely
an ordinary vampire.

319
00:16:29,890 --> 00:16:32,159
billie Jean:
You’d best stay out of our way,

320
00:16:32,192 --> 00:16:33,827
or we might end up killing you.

321
00:16:33,861 --> 00:16:37,164
d’arby: Do try
to behave yourself, loser.

322
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:39,299
( Vampire groans )

323
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:42,970
i’ll be the one
who finishes off jotaro.

324
00:16:43,003 --> 00:16:45,205
♪

325
00:16:47,708 --> 00:16:49,376
( Kakyoin gasps ) Stop.

326
00:16:49,409 --> 00:16:50,911
There’s something
up ahead to the right.

327
00:16:50,944 --> 00:16:52,846
( Both grunt )

328
00:16:57,084 --> 00:16:59,086
( Woman gasping )

329
00:17:01,955 --> 00:17:03,223
Joseph: A woman.

330
00:17:03,257 --> 00:17:05,326
( Woman screams )

331
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,794
Please have mercy on me.

332
00:17:06,827 --> 00:17:09,396
I’m begging you,
don’t suck my blood!

333
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:10,463
Anything but that!

334
00:17:10,497 --> 00:17:12,733
- Joseph: Huh?
- ( Woman crying )

335
00:17:12,766 --> 00:17:14,901
I swear i’ll do
whatever you want.

336
00:17:14,935 --> 00:17:18,038
Just let me live.
That’s all i’m asking.

337
00:17:18,071 --> 00:17:20,774
Joseph: Hey, easy now.

338
00:17:20,807 --> 00:17:22,309
You need to calm down.

339
00:17:22,342 --> 00:17:24,044
Woman: I won’t run away anymore.

340
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:26,413
You can trust me.
Please have mercy.

341
00:17:26,446 --> 00:17:28,782
Joseph: Just breathe.
We aren’t dio’s minions,

342
00:17:28,815 --> 00:17:31,151
and we’re
certainly not vampires.

343
00:17:31,185 --> 00:17:35,322
We’re the good guys, so just
calm down, and let us help you.

344
00:17:35,355 --> 00:17:36,756
Woman: You’re good guys?

345
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:39,359
( Gasps ) Good guys?

346
00:17:39,393 --> 00:17:41,862
you’re really
not those evil vampires?

347
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:44,364
You’re actually going to help me
get away from here?

348
00:17:44,398 --> 00:17:47,134
Jotaro: That’s right.
we’re good.

349
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:48,168
( Woman sighs )

350
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,039
( Groans )

351
00:17:52,072 --> 00:17:53,507
Jotaro: Real good...

352
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:55,909
At punchin’ evil in the face.

353
00:17:55,943 --> 00:17:56,911
( Woman squeals )

354
00:17:56,944 --> 00:17:58,379
Joseph: If you still want help,

355
00:17:58,412 --> 00:18:00,180
we’ll be happy to oblige.

356
00:18:00,214 --> 00:18:02,817
We’ll help by sending you
on a one-way trip to hell.

357
00:18:02,850 --> 00:18:04,919
- Sound good, kakyoin?
- ( Kakyoin grunts )

358
00:18:04,952 --> 00:18:06,954
( Woman groaning )

359
00:18:08,355 --> 00:18:10,324
Vampire: How? Damn it.

360
00:18:10,357 --> 00:18:13,126
How? Tell me. How? How?

361
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:15,896
How did you figure it out?

362
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:18,331
My power is impossible to crack!

363
00:18:18,365 --> 00:18:20,300
Kakyoin: Would this power
have anything to do

364
00:18:20,334 --> 00:18:22,536
with the face of a woman
on the back of your head?

365
00:18:22,569 --> 00:18:24,371
Joseph: For future reference,
when you flip your head,

366
00:18:24,404 --> 00:18:26,072
you should make sure
your hands match, too.

367
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:28,041
- Vampire: Eh?
- Woman: Huh?

368
00:18:28,075 --> 00:18:29,276
Both: Eh?

369
00:18:29,309 --> 00:18:31,478
( Vampire gasps )
Shit. You’re right.

370
00:18:31,512 --> 00:18:34,215
I never noticed.
I’m an idiot!

371
00:18:34,248 --> 00:18:36,083
Jotaro: No, you’re a loser.

372
00:18:36,116 --> 00:18:38,552
Now where is dio’s room?
out with it.

373
00:18:38,585 --> 00:18:41,021
Kakyoin: Jotaro, try not
to knock him unconscious.

374
00:18:41,054 --> 00:18:42,856
He can take us to dio.

375
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:44,091
( Vampire growls )

376
00:18:44,124 --> 00:18:47,094
how dare you?
Don’t you call me that.

377
00:18:47,127 --> 00:18:49,062
You’re just like
those other guys,

378
00:18:49,096 --> 00:18:50,864
so you’ll meet the same fate.

379
00:18:51,865 --> 00:18:53,133
I’ll kill you!

380
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:54,935
Lord dio’s power’s
made me immortal,

381
00:18:54,968 --> 00:18:57,904
and i’ll use all of it
to rip you to pieces!

382
00:18:57,938 --> 00:19:00,474
( Hisses )

383
00:19:00,507 --> 00:19:01,475
Eh?

384
00:19:01,508 --> 00:19:03,310
Jotaro: So unless I heard wrong,

385
00:19:03,343 --> 00:19:05,111
you just said
you were an immortal,

386
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:07,414
so you’re a vampire like dio,

387
00:19:07,447 --> 00:19:10,817
in which case, I can use you
as a practice dummy

388
00:19:10,851 --> 00:19:12,820
for when I fight
against the real thing.

389
00:19:12,853 --> 00:19:14,855
Joseph: Eh? Oh, my god.

390
00:19:14,888 --> 00:19:17,824
( Star platinum yelling )

391
00:19:17,858 --> 00:19:18,826
( Vampire screams )

392
00:19:18,859 --> 00:19:21,128
( Grunting )

393
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:28,568
Jotaro: So you
really are immortal.

394
00:19:28,602 --> 00:19:32,005
vampire or not, we can
still rip you into little pieces

395
00:19:32,039 --> 00:19:33,841
and scatter them
around the room.

396
00:19:33,874 --> 00:19:36,443
Well, are you takin’ us
to dio or not?

397
00:19:36,476 --> 00:19:38,445
The sun is about to set.

398
00:19:38,478 --> 00:19:41,414
Vampire: Okay, but can I
at least ask you one thing?

399
00:19:41,448 --> 00:19:42,516
Jotaro: Hmm?

400
00:19:42,549 --> 00:19:44,251
vampire:
How the hell did you know

401
00:19:44,284 --> 00:19:46,520
the other stand users
used to call me "loser"?

402
00:19:48,155 --> 00:19:50,124
Jotaro: Oh, man. Good grief.

403
00:19:52,559 --> 00:19:54,561
♪

404
00:21:23,584 --> 00:21:26,087
( Footsteps echoing )

405
00:21:26,119 --> 00:21:28,722
( Polnareff winces )
I gotta hand it to him.

406
00:21:28,755 --> 00:21:31,358
dio’s got
some pretty nice curtains.

407
00:21:32,426 --> 00:21:34,328
( Winces )

408
00:21:34,361 --> 00:21:38,999
All right, now I can walk and
even jump around if I need to.

409
00:21:39,032 --> 00:21:40,567
It still hurts a bit,

410
00:21:40,601 --> 00:21:43,971
but now’s not the time
to worry about a little pain.

411
00:21:44,004 --> 00:21:45,372
Hmm?

412
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:49,142
♪

413
00:21:51,378 --> 00:21:54,514
Dio: Ah, greetings, polnareff.

414
00:21:54,548 --> 00:21:56,450
What a pleasant surprise.

415
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:58,552
Polnareff: Dio.

416
00:21:58,585 --> 00:22:01,021
At last.

